    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>spelt </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>to the pot with the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook, covered, for 30 min or until tender (it will still have a slight bite when cooked)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1693405454664-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
