            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining garlic</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your <strong>parsley oil</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into 3 slices per person</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced ciabatta</strong> to a separate baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 5-6 min or until the ciabatta is starting to brown – these are your <strong>ciabatta toasts</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
